ed weights.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.71,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Pagination returns the correct page of results, with stable ordering — requesting page 2 twice returns identical results if the underlying data hasn't changed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Stability depends on sort key + pagination logic together. Unit tests of paginator can miss nondeterministic upstream ordering.","test_description":"Generate recommendations with deterministic fixture data and request page 2 twice through the full service method/repository path. Assert identical ordered IDs and correct slice boundaries.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The recommendation algorithm surfaces at least one product from a category the user hasn't browsed before (serendipity requirement), avoiding a filter bubble.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a policy constraint enforced during candidate selection/reranking; failures come from interaction between personalization and diversity logic.","test_description":"Use fixtures where user history covers categories X/Y and candidate pool includes X/Y/Z. Run recommendation flow and assert at least one top-N result is from unseen category Z while relevance constraints still hold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.16,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A new user with no purchase or browsing history receives recommendations based on overall popularity rather than an empty result set.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Cold-start behavior depends on fallback routing and popularity source wiring; unit tests can miss null-state path integration bug